  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "freetype security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for freetype is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "FreeType is written in C, designed to be small,efficient, highly customizable, and portable while capable of producing high-quality output (glyph images) of most vector and bitmap font formats\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nAn integer overflow in the tt_var_load_item_variation_store function of the Freetype library in versions 2.13.2 and 2.13.3 may allow for an out of bounds read operation when parsing HVAR/VVAR/MVAR tables in OpenType variable fonts. This issue is fixed in version 2.14.2.(CVE-2026-23865)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for freetype is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "freetype",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
